SerialICE Controller
SerialICE Controller
 

The SerialICE Monitor (on the SerialICE Controller) accepts commands from the 
Host,
and issues commands to the Target via a
Driver.

SerialICE supports the following boards for use as a SerialICE Controller.

BDMR400x Evaluation Board

  »  Insert the four flash memories containing the SerialICE Monitor in U8, 
	U19, U29, and U40.
  »  Connect a serial cable from U28 to the host.
  »  Connect a null-modem serial cable from U43 to the 
	target.

Nitro (4010) Evaluation Board

  »  Insert the flash memory containing the SerialICE Monitor in U18.
  »  Connect a serial cable from J18 to the host.
  »  Connect a null-modem serial cable from J17 to the 
	target.

